message: "If you use Nous in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Nous: Formally-Grounded Detection of Epistemic Closure Violations in LLM Agent Reasoning Traces"
version: 0.4.0
date-released: "2026-04-10"
url: "https://github.com/sayang7/nous"
repository-code: "https://github.com/sayang7/nous"
license: MIT
authors:
  - family-names: Gupta
    given-names: Sayan
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0000-0000-0000"
abstract: >
  Nous is a formal reasoning integrity engine for AI agents. It detects epistemic
  closure violations — cases where an agent's actions contradict the logical
  consequences of its own stated beliefs — using Kripke semantics, a commitment
  graph, and Lean 4 soundness proofs. On a 40-task benchmark, Nous achieves
  0.889 precision and 0.800 recall (F1 = 0.842).
keywords:
  - epistemic logic
  - LLM agents
  - reasoning integrity
  - formal verification
  - Kripke semantics
  - belief-action coherence
  - AI safety
